 operated by appalachian power company is licensed by the federal energy regulatory commission ferc as project no the claytor project consists of a concrete gravity dam with gated spillway integral intake and powerhouse switching equipment appurtenant facilities and the reservoir httpwwwclaytorhydrocom kanawha hydro projects  appalachian power is seeking to relicense the londonmarmet and winfield hydroelectric projects in consultation with representatives from various state and federal agencies as well as local governments nongovernmental organizations and the public httpwwwkanawhahydrocom smith mountain project  smith mountain is a pumped storage project that utilizes an upper reservoir smith mountain lake and a lower reservoir leesville lake httpwwwsmithmtncom other aep sites aep economic development  aeps professional economic development staff works strategically with many organizations communities and allies to provide smart and effective business opportunities to both prospective and existing businesses and industries we provide information on available sites and buildings along with community profiles and many years of experience in the communities we serve we also provide turnkey engineering construction procurement and maintenance services to commercial and industrial customers electric cooperatives and municipal utilities httpwwwaepedcom aep electronic data interchange  organizations that exchange business documents such as invoices or purchase orders via paper with aep can increase the reliability of those transactions while decreasing business costs through electronic data interchange or edi httpwwwaepedicom aep surplus  aep offers prospective buyers an opportunity to buy or bid on obsolete used or excess equipment and materials from various sites within our operating territory httpwwwaepsurpluscom aep sustainability  aeps corporate sustainability website developed to allow for more comprehenseive integrated reporting on our total performance we report using the global reporting initiative gri protocol and our report is checked by gri httpwwwaepsustainabilitycom dolan technology center  aeps dolan technology center offers a staff of flexible resourceful experts in instrumentation developmentimplementation test formulationimplementation and technical support dolan technology center brings to your project expertise gained from the long history and vast knowledge of supporting aeps distribution transmission and generation companies along with a keen focus on new electrotechnology developments httpwwwdolantechcentercom united sciences testing inc  usti performs plant emissions flow monitoring employing an automated process that eliminates or significantly reduces overreporting of emissions thereby saving time and money httpwwwustiratacom joint transmission projects electric transmission texas  electric transmission texas llc ett is a joint venture between aep and midamerican energy holdings company which will build transmission projects within the electric reliability council of texas ercot httpwwwettexascom pioneer transmission  pioneer transmission llc is a joint venture formed by duke energy and american electric power aep to build and operate  miles of extrahighvoltage kilovolt kv transmission lines and related facilities in indiana httpwwwpnrtransmissioncom rite line transmission  reliability interregional transmission extension or rite line is a joint venture formed by exelon corporation and electric transmission america eta  a joint venture of subsidiaries of american electric power and midamerican energy holdings  to build and operate approximately  miles of highvoltage transmission lines and related facilities in indiana and illinois httpwwwritelinetranscocom transource energy  transource a partnership between aep and great plains energy is dedicated to investing in and building new electric transmission infrastructure in a competitive marketplace the focus of transource is the development of costeffective transmission solutions initially within the pjm interconnection southwest power pool spp and the midwest independent system operator miso regions httpwwwtransourceenergycom employee  retiree sites aepnowcom employees only  aep now is the official corporate intranet internal web site at aep offering corporate news and other information for employees aepnowcom enables remote access to aep now and hr now aepretireescom  the official web site dedicated to serving retirees and other alumni of american electric power providing relevant news and announcements from aep updates about the people who have served aep and links to other related web sites customer service join our conversations on twitter and facebook learn more about us through youtube and flickr american electric power delivers electricity to approximately five million residential commercial and industrial customers in the united states our service territory includes portions of arkansas indiana kentucky louisiana michigan ohio oklahoma tennessee texas virginia and west virginia aep websites social media back to the top home investors news releases  email alerts events presentations  webcasts sec filings  other financial reports current regulatory activity corporate leaders  governance buy and manage aep stock stock history  dividends shareholder contact  faqs newsroom corporate news releases media relations contacts regional utility news facts  leadership other industry resources subscribe to news alerts financialinvestors information environment corporate accountability report climate change emissions  compliance environmental news conservation  outdoor recreation falconcam community aep foundation corporate giving guidelines community affairs  economic development safety  health for teachers  students conservation  outdoor recreation community connections report careers current job openings college coops  internships taking an employment test aeps employment process why aep aep locations pay and benefits workli